
Overview of noun clove

The noun clove has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                        
1. clove -- (aromatic flower bud of a clove tree; yields a spice)
2. clove, clove tree, Syzygium aromaticum, Eugenia aromaticum, Eugenia caryophyllatum -- (moderate sized very symmetrical red-flowered evergreen widely cultivated in the tropics for its flower buds which are source of cloves)
3. clove, garlic clove -- (one of the small bulblets that can be split off of the axis of a larger garlic bulb)
4. clove -- (spice from dried unopened flower bud of the clove tree; used whole or ground)

